1 (3) A resident bidder must be allowed preference under subsection (1)(a) except if, for contracts
2 awarded under this chapter, the lowest bidder:
3 (a) has not performed on a prior contract;
4 (b) has requested more than two extensions on a contract; or
5 (c) has failed to perform warranty work on a prior contract.
6 (4) If the situations described in subsection (3) occur, a contract awarded to the lowest bidder may
7 be canceled and given to the second lowest bidder."
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Appropriation. There is appropriated $500 from the general fund to the
10 department of administration for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for the purposes of updating educational
11 materials to distribute to the public related to the changes outlined in [section 1].
